==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Emollescence
<hw>Em`ol*les"cence</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>e</ets> out + <ets>mollescere</ets>, incho. fr. <ets>mollere</ets>
to be soft, <ets>mollis</ets> soft.]</ety> <def>That degree of softness
in a body beginning to melt which alters its shape; the first or lowest
degree of fusibility.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Emolliate</ent>⟦br⟧
